## chosen

The `/chosen` node does not represent a real device in the system but describes parameters chosen or specified by the system firmware at run time. It shall be a child of the root node.

Common properties in `/chosen`:

- `bootargs` — kernel boot arguments string
- `stdout-path` — path (or alias) to the boot console output device
- `stdin-path` — path (or alias) to the boot console input device

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550-qrd.dts */
chosen {
    stdout-path = "serial0:115200n8";
};

/* DTS spec example */
chosen {
    bootargs = "root=/dev/nfs rw nfsroot=192.168.1.1 console=ttyS0,115200";
};
```
